name: KASIKU lawar Kuir
address: No Jl. Prof. Dr. Ida Bagus Mantra No.708, Takmung, Kec. Banjarangkan, Kabupaten Klungkung, Bali 80752, Indonesia
review 1:
Delicious yet unpretentious.

A set menu of lawar kuir is for IDR 22k only, plus 5k if you order drinks.

Kuir is Balinese word for muscovy duck, while lawar is a vegetable side dish. Here, you will be served a set menu of lawar kuir including steamed white rice and a bowl of vegetable soup. Everything is cooked in Balinese spices with moderate level of spiciness.

The place is comfortable and the service is quick. You might expect to wait for a while during lunch hour, though.
review 2:
Nice litlle Warung.
Food was Verry delicious and tasteful.

Warung Kasiku special is local muskus duck
Two person with drink 60 idr
review 3: They only do one dish here and it's the duck. You get sate, duck mix, soup and rice for about $2.50. It's delicious homestyle local food. Owner is also very friendly.
review 4:
This place has been around for ages. Famous with it's Lawar Kuwir (duck?)

Price is very reasonable and clean as well.

Very close to Lepang Beach and Wyndham Taman Sari Jiivva Resort
review 5: delicious food, good price, good location

name: Warung Taman Sari Lepang
address: Jl. Prof. Dr. Ida Bagus Mantra, lepang, Takmung, Kec. Banjarangkan, Kabupaten Klungkung, Bali 80752, Indonesia
review 1: This is a traditional warung along the eastern highway near the Lepang turnoff. It has a limited menu with mainly fish and chicken, indonesian cooking style. Very clean place, good service and the food tasted great. Not expensive. Parking easy. Open from 9 to 9. The place is a bit noisy from the traffic of the highway passing by.
review 2: Tasty food at cheap price. Gurami Nyat nyat was tasty
review 3: This Resto is a typical excellent place to eat Indonesian food at it's best. The homemade sambal bawang is to die for. Our meals and drinks for 3 people was less than $10 (Rp 100k).
review 4: Very tasty food and prices are cheap. Great place for dining.

name: Warung Makan Pak Ngurah
address: Jl. Prof. Dr. Ida Bagus Mantra No.708, Takmung, Kec. Banjarangkan, Kabupaten Klungkung, Bali 80752, Indonesia
review 1:
My husband and myself had an awesome experience of tasting local food.
The table was cleaned as we walked in to sit down, there was a sink to wash your hands before eating.
The service was friendly, polite and happy to go above and beyond my expectations. I had a vegetable meal as a side dish, my main meal was a fried chicken, rice with salad.
It was our first time eating at a local food service and we are so glad we came here first.
Not only was it delicious but extremely affordable at $2.50(Australian)per person including our drink of choice. We will definitely be coming back before we leave the area to enjoy more dishes.
review 2: I ordered a package of ikan bakar. It was delicious. I love the plecing kangkung and the bakso. The place is clean enough. There are some delicious chips. The staffs were also good and kind. They treated the customer well. About the price, it's quite cheap. Worth it lah di kantong.
review 3: We have eaten here a couple of times.  Great food, good portion size and awesome customer service.
review 4: A local street food place where the locals eat. Very reasonable price.
